INSERT INTO 
    recipes (name, description, ingredients, prep_time, cooking_time, serving)
VALUES
    ('Beef Burrito', 'A versatile and flavorful Mexican-inspired dish that typically consists of a highly seasoned beef filling, which is the main flavor component of the burrito. The beef filling is often seasoned with a homemade spice mix, providing a rich and juicy flavor to the burrito. Additionally, the beef filling contributes to the wetness of the burrito and mixes through the other ingredients when rolled up. The burrito is typically wrapped in a flour tortilla and can be topped with additional ingredients such as taco sauce, refried beans, cheese, and various vegetables. It can also be served with toppings like guacamole, sour cream, and cilantro. The burrito can be baked to melt the cheese and enhance the flavors of the filling. This dish offers a convenient freezer standby and can be easily reheated. The recipe is highly customizable, allowing for the addition of various ingredients based on personal preferences. Overall, the beef burrito provides a delicious and satisfying meal that can be enjoyed fresh or frozen.', '1 pound ground beef, 1 small onion, diced, 2 cloves garlic, minced, 1 bell pepper, diced (any color you prefer), 1 can (15 ounces) black beans, drained and rinsed, 1 cup cooked rice, 1 cup shredded cheese (such as cheddar or Monterey Jack), 1 tablespoon olive oil, 1 tablespoon chili powder, 1 teaspoon ground cumin, and 6-8 large flour tortillas', '20 minutes', '30 minutes', '4'),
    ('Veggie Lo Mein', 'A delightful and versatile dish that brings together a colorful array of fresh vegetables and soft, slurpy noodles. This quick and easy meal is perfect for a light weekday lunch or a quick dinner, offering a satisfying and healthy option for vegetarians and veggie lovers alike. The dish typically features a savory and sweet sauce, which is stir-fried with the noodles and an abundance of fresh produce, such as mushrooms, shredded cabbage, carrots, snow peas, bell peppers, and more. The dish is highly adaptable and customizable, allowing for the addition of various seasonal vegetables and protein options like crispy tofu, chicken breast, or shrimp. Veggie Lo Mein can be made in under 30 minutes, making it a convenient and flavorful choice for a homemade meal. It''s a great way to pack a ton of fresh produce into a dish that''s both delicious and nutritious. Whether enjoyed as a main course or as a side, Veggie Lo Mein offers a delightful combination of flavors and textures that''s sure to please the whole family.', '8 ounces of lo mein noodles or any other type of Chinese egg noodles, 2 tablespoons vegetable oil, 2 cloves garlic, minced, 1 tablespoon ginger, minced 1 medium carrot, julienned or thinly sliced, 1 bell pepper, thinly sliced (any color you prefer), 1 small onion, thinly sliced, 1 cup sliced mushrooms (such as shiitake or button mushrooms), 1 cup broccoli florets, 1 cup snap peas or snow peas, trimmed, 2 tablespoons soy sauce (or more to taste), 1 tablespoon oyster sauce (optional, for added flavor), 1 teaspoon sesame oil, 1 teaspoon cornstarch mixed with 2 tablespoons water (optional, for thickening the sauce), Salt and pepper to taste, Optional garnishes: sliced green onions, sesame seeds, crushed red pepper flakes', '10 minutes', '20 minutes', '4'),
    ('No-Bake Nutella Brownies', 'No-bake Nutella brownies are a decadent and indulgent treat that require no oven time, making them perfect for satisfying your sweet tooth with minimal effort. These brownies are made with just a few simple ingredients, including creamy Nutella, crushed chocolate wafer cookies or graham crackers, and optional additions like chopped nuts for extra crunch. The mixture is pressed into a pan, chilled until firm, and then cut into delicious squares or bars. With their rich chocolate-hazelnut flavor and fudgy texture, these no-bake Nutella brownies are sure to be a hit at any gathering or as a quick and easy dessert for yourself.', '1 cup Nutella (or any chocolate hazelnut spread), 2 cups crushed chocolate wafer cookies or graham crackers, 1/2 cup chopped nuts (such as walnuts or hazelnuts), optional, 1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder (optional, for extra chocolate flavor), 1/4 cup powdered sugar (optional, for extra sweetness), Pinch of salt (optional, to enhance flavors), 1/4 cup milk (add more if needed)', '20 minutes', '5 minutes', '9' );